  "body": "Hello! I'm trying to create horizontal scroll and having an issue. I create two buttons and for each button I add events onTouchStart, onTouchEnd and onTouchCancel. When event onTouchStart triggers, I change margin for container which contains all scrollable elements. And onTouchEnd and onTouchCancel need to stop this scroll. But these events don't trigger and I can't stop scroll. In which cases events may not trigger? I use chrome v40, OS Ubuntu 14.01, react 15.0.2. I tested it in Chrome device mode.\n\nThis is my code: \n\n``` js\n<button\n  ref=\"scrollLeft\"\n  onMouseDown={this.scrollLeft}\n  onTouchStart={this.scrollLeft}\n  onMouseLeave={this.stopLeftScroll}\n  onTouchEnd={this.stopLeftScroll}\n  onTouchCancel={this.stopLeftScroll}\n  className={cx(\n    'left',\n    styles.scrollButton,\n    styles.leftScrollBut,\n    {\n      [styles.enable]: shouldRenderArrows,\n      [styles.disable]: !shouldRenderArrows,\n    }\n  )}\n>\n</button>\n```\n",
